<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
  <title>About — Used Car Dealership</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/main.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/header', { user: user }) %>

  <main>
    <section>
      <h2>About This Project</h2>
      <p>
        This web application is a course project for CSE 340 that models a small used car
        dealership. It demonstrates server-side rendering with Express and EJS, session-based
        authentication, role-based authorization, a PostgreSQL-backed data model, and a
        multi-stage service request workflow.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Owner</strong>: Owner One — manages inventory, categories, and employee accounts.<br />
        <strong>Employees</strong>: Manage vehicle details, moderate reviews, and handle service requests.<br />
        <strong>Customers</strong>: Browse vehicles, leave reviews, and submit service requests for their vehicles.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Use the <a href="/contact">contact form</a> to send us a message. Contact submissions are saved to the database and visible to employees in the dashboard.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
